description:
**Position Summary**  

Professional Word Processing Specialist with a minimum of seven years of experience preferably in the WP Department of a law firm. This individual should have demonstrated proficiency in document production, understand urgency, be flexible and be able to communicate with all levels at the firm.




**Duties and Responsibilities include and are not limited to:**  

Technical
* turn-around documents and projects accurately and expeditiously;
* follow Best Practice;
* QA check own work (no proofreader on staff);
* research new projects; create quick guides when new projects warrant it;
* troubleshoot for self and Users
* will be trained to work on projects for other departments

Administrative
* record all activity in the WP Traffic Log (incoming/outgoing work, times worked);
* must understand, adhere to protocols, procedures and policies at Firm and Department levels;
* monitor the WP email production Inbox and Conflicts email production Inbox
* prioritize jobs by deadline; negotiate deadlines when necessary
* follow delivery and special instructions provided by Users;
* check the WP Inbox to ensure all requests have been handled (ensure nothing is missed)
* flexibility to attend training sessions outside of the regular shift as needed;

**Position Specific Skills and Requirements**
* typing speed: 75+ wpm with 5 (or fewer) error count
* speed and accuracy are of utmost importance. (No proofreaders to check work.)
* proficiency in advance features and troubleshooting in the following applications:
* Windows 10
* Office 365 (Word, Excel, PowerPoint) Advance functions
* Adobe Acrobat
* OmniPage
* Best Authority
* edit, input, format in full (clean up, style, code) documents;
* transcribe using Philips or typing live dictation;
* hands-on experience with large documents and projects.

**Requirements:**
* minimum of seven years of experience as a Word Processor (preferably in a large law firm);
* regular attendance and punctuality;
* overtime and working on some Firm-observed holidays is a job requirement;
* enthusiastic to accept new responsibilities

**Education and General Requirements*** must have a good command of English;
* BA degree, certificates are a plus
* minimum of seven years of hands-on experience as a Word Processor preferably in a law firm



All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment and will not be discriminated against on the basis of race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, national origin, age, disability, or protected veteran status. Hughes Hubbard & Reed takes affirmative action in support of its policy to and advance in employment individuals who are minorities, women, protected veterans, and individuals with disabilities. VEVRAA Federal Contractor  

